<div class="t m308 x5d h1 y238 ff1 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">3. </div><div class="t ma66 x29 h1 y8a8 ff1 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">What mode of baptism was used by John in baptizing Jesus? </div><div class="t mea2 x11 h1 y253 ff1 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Where was He baptized? Matt. 3:16: Mark 1:5, 9. </div><div class="t m2a0 x14 he y490 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">NorE.-Jesus was baptized of John in Jordan. He &quot;went up straightway </div><div class="t m1062 x11 he y1e1 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">out of the water.&quot; The baptism of Christ was by immersion. No other method </div><div class="t m1e8 x11 he y186 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">of water baptism is taught in the Bible. </div><div class="t m486 x5d h1 y8a9 ff1 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">4. </div><div class="t m115f x29 h1 y239 ff1 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">What public announcement was made by God at Jesus&apos; baptism? </div><div class="t m1144 x11 h1 y507 ff1 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Matt. 3:17. </div><div class="t mea4 x14 he y343 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">NOTE.-&quot;These words of confirmation were given to inspire faith in those </div><div class="t m97 x11 he y463 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">who witnessed the scene, and to strengthen the Saviour for His mission.&quot;-</div><div class="t m5c2 x27 h21 y85 ff6 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">&quot;The Desire of Ages,&quot; </div><div class="t m1180 x30 h1 y85 ff1 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">p. </div><div class="t m1500 x8e he y85 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">112. </div><div class="t m486 x5d h1 yca ff1 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">5. </div><div class="t mcdc x36 h1 y34 ff1 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Where else did John baptize? Why? John 3:23. </div><div class="t m326 x5d h1 y16c ff1 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">6. </div><div class="t m3d5 x36 h1 y60a ff1 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">How did he interpret the baptismal experience of Christ? John </div><div class="t mf9b x11 h1 y447 ff1 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">1 :31 -34. </div><div class="t m30c9 x99 h1 ye5e ff1 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">I </div><div class="t m2c3b x2a h25 ye5e ff4 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws